text: Skaraborg County () was a county in southern Sweden. The seat was first in Skara, then in Mariestad from 1660. It was established in 1634, and disestablished on 31 December 1997, following the establishment of Västra Götaland County. == Governors == *Harald Strömfelt (1695–1707) *Carl Gustaf Soop (1707–1711) *Germund Cederhielm d.ä.
